        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". לאמר, saying, i.e., at the consecration of this house, having expressed the confident hope contained in the following words (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 20:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). In this verse, the cases enumerated in Solomon's dedicatory prayer, in which supplication is made that God would hear in the temple, are briefly summed up. By referring to that prayer, Jehoshaphat presupposes that Jahve had promised that He would answer prayer offered there, since He had filled the temple with His glory; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 7:1-3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The name שׁפות, which occurs only here, between דּבר and חרב, denotes in this connection a punitive judgment. ",
        "children": []
      }
